1
00:00:09,740 --> 00:00:13,815
Goal and scope definition.

2
00:00:13,815 --> 00:00:18,840
Why on earth do we spend
an entire LCA phase,

3
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:25,360
an entire one force of my LCA
just to scope the problem?

4
00:00:25,360 --> 00:00:28,480
That's because a problem

5
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:31,360
which is well-defined
is half solved.

6
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:35,485
It's really crucial, as we
saw in the popcorn example,

7
00:00:35,485 --> 00:00:37,510
that we define well

8
00:00:37,510 --> 00:00:40,450
the basis for comparison,
the metric used,

9
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:42,185
the system boundaries,

10
00:00:42,185 --> 00:00:45,910
and that's why this goal and
scope definition is perhaps

11
00:00:45,910 --> 00:00:48,260
the most important phase and

12
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:52,805
also sometimes the most
problematic phase in LCA.

13
00:00:52,805 --> 00:00:56,585
We start now and we'll spend

14
00:00:56,585 --> 00:01:00,710
some time on the goal
and scope definition to

15
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:03,320
really define the
different element

16
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:05,734
which serves the basis
then to calculate

17
00:01:05,734 --> 00:01:08,600
inventory of extraction
and impacts which

18
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:12,095
are related to the
problem definition.

19
00:01:12,095 --> 00:01:14,810
Our learning objective
for today are to

20
00:01:14,810 --> 00:01:17,780
define the goal and
scope of an LCA and for

21
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:20,525
this particular
lecture to identify

22
00:01:20,525 --> 00:01:24,500
the intended use and
user of the LCA,

23
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,855
the decision context situation,

24
00:01:26,855 --> 00:01:30,270
and the intended audience.

25
00:01:30,650 --> 00:01:35,190
ISO 14044 give rule

26
00:01:35,190 --> 00:01:39,080
and say that in defining
the goal of an LCA,

27
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:45,315
the following item shall be
unambiguously stated and

28
00:01:45,315 --> 00:01:48,990
when ISO said shall and

29
00:01:48,990 --> 00:01:53,145
not can that mean this
is a requirement.

30
00:01:53,145 --> 00:01:55,865
If you want your LCA

31
00:01:55,865 --> 00:01:59,000
to be ISO compliant
and ISO compatible,

32
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,545
you need to do that,

33
00:02:00,545 --> 00:02:01,730
otherwise, you're
not.

34
00:02:01,730 --> 00:02:03,080
If these points are not

35
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:05,450
explicitly in your
report you're out,

36
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:07,880
reviewer will not give

37
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:11,675
you the blessing for an
ISO compliance study.

38
00:02:11,675 --> 00:02:14,960
You need to define your
intended application,

39
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,995
why you're carrying
out the study,

40
00:02:17,995 --> 00:02:20,810
who is the intended
audience to whom

41
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:24,245
the results of the study are
intended to be communicated,

42
00:02:24,245 --> 00:02:26,900
and whether the
results are intended

43
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:29,120
to be used in a
comparative assertion,

44
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,520
meaning comparing
your product with

45
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:35,300
another product explicitly
or even implicitly,

46
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:39,535
and which is intended to be
disclosed to the public.

47
00:02:39,535 --> 00:02:43,140
Let's take the example of

48
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:50,030
light bulbs and we will
define the scope and

49
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:52,850
the goal of my LCA for typically

50
00:02:52,850 --> 00:02:56,420
comparing incandescent
light bulb

51
00:02:56,420 --> 00:03:00,535
with fluorescent or
an LED light bulb.

52
00:03:00,535 --> 00:03:04,180
Let's think what would

53
00:03:04,180 --> 00:03:07,525
be the objective and
reason for our study.

54
00:03:07,525 --> 00:03:10,180
Could be different things
in general for an LCA,

55
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:12,925
could be product information,

56
00:03:12,925 --> 00:03:15,715
product development
within the company,

57
00:03:15,715 --> 00:03:18,565
defined policy and strategy at

58
00:03:18,565 --> 00:03:21,970
governmental or
business level or

59
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:25,675
regulation at a
governmental level.

60
00:03:25,675 --> 00:03:27,240
In our case here,

61
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,410
we can, for example,

62
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:32,830
provide product information
to select what is

63
00:03:32,830 --> 00:03:34,840
the most suitable type of

64
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:37,310
light bulb for a
given application.

65
00:03:37,310 --> 00:03:40,310
Typically our targeted
audience here

66
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:43,700
will be consumers
whereas other LCA could

67
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:47,149
be focused on the
governmental body or internal

68
00:03:47,149 --> 00:03:51,230
also for product development
inside the company.

69
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:54,440
Then we need to
define the actors and

70
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:56,300
the actors is a sponsor of

71
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:58,715
the study, the
different authors.

72
00:03:58,715 --> 00:04:00,140
We'll see what is

73
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:03,695
an advisory board and peer
reviewer in a minute.

74
00:04:03,695 --> 00:04:09,140
The more you involve independent
entities in your work,

75
00:04:09,140 --> 00:04:13,405
you will enhance the
credibility of your study.

76
00:04:13,405 --> 00:04:19,165
Let's look in further detail
about these actors here.

77
00:04:19,165 --> 00:04:22,760
The identity of the
main stakeholders

78
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:25,895
and their addresses
should be provided.

79
00:04:25,895 --> 00:04:27,980
Let's say for sponsor,

80
00:04:27,980 --> 00:04:31,790
typically for this
light bulb study,

81
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:34,055
we would have
consumer association.

82
00:04:34,055 --> 00:04:36,500
The author analyst,
of course, it's you,

83
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:43,940
EHS672 consultant who will
become expert in a few weeks.

84
00:04:43,940 --> 00:04:46,940
That's your role as in

85
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:50,090
your case study to
carry such a study.

86
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:52,325
Optional advisory board.

87
00:04:52,325 --> 00:04:54,725
What is the role of
an advisory board?

88
00:04:54,725 --> 00:04:58,010
It's to provide
you the knowledge

89
00:04:58,010 --> 00:05:01,340
from different stakeholder
and ensure that

90
00:05:01,340 --> 00:05:04,730
all the hypotheses are setup in

91
00:05:04,730 --> 00:05:08,990
a fair way and often you
will involve people,

92
00:05:08,990 --> 00:05:11,180
for example, here
representative from

93
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:13,355
the bulb manufacturer like

94
00:05:13,355 --> 00:05:16,130
astronomer Phillips
or General Electric.

95
00:05:16,130 --> 00:05:18,815
The electricity company would
be perhaps interesting,

96
00:05:18,815 --> 00:05:22,355
like DTE, the USEPA,

97
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:25,070
or representative from an NGO

98
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:26,660
like environmental defense or

99
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:31,250
different NGO and if you're
a consumer association,

100
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,335
you certainly will have someone

101
00:05:33,335 --> 00:05:37,270
representing the consumer
association in that.

102
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:39,130
When you select these people,

103
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:43,300
it's nice in fact to select
people who are potentially

104
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:48,950
on the other side of the study.

105
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:52,000
It's nice when you're
on the consumer side

106
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,400
to have the bulb
manufacturer represented.

107
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:57,425
Now, who do you choose in there?

108
00:05:57,425 --> 00:05:59,940
Two criteria to
choose the people.

109
00:05:59,940 --> 00:06:02,470
Knowledgeable, you want people

110
00:06:02,470 --> 00:06:05,229
who bring knowledge and
who bring insights.

111
00:06:05,229 --> 00:06:07,270
In particular, you're
not a specialist

112
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:09,940
usually from the domain
when you do an LCA

113
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:12,790
so you need to bring people who

114
00:06:12,790 --> 00:06:16,195
know about bulb and
will give you insight,

115
00:06:16,195 --> 00:06:18,685
will indicate where to
find some of the data,

116
00:06:18,685 --> 00:06:22,055
will help you for that.

117
00:06:22,055 --> 00:06:26,720
Second, you want them to
be open-minded experts.

118
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,840
What I mean by that is you
don't want someone who has

119
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:34,810
decided before the study
what the results should be.

120
00:06:34,810 --> 00:06:37,260
You need people who,

121
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:38,700
looking at the evidences,

122
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,050
looking at the science,

123
00:06:40,050 --> 00:06:44,120
can change their
mind while still

124
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:48,555
representing a
certain stakeholder,

125
00:06:48,555 --> 00:06:50,345
and because if this person

126
00:06:50,345 --> 00:06:52,925
is well recognized
in his domain,

127
00:06:52,925 --> 00:06:56,580
it will give you credibility
and avoid that at the end,

128
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:58,130
people say, they didn't

129
00:06:58,130 --> 00:07:02,490
consider one of the main
problem in our story.

130
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:05,974
I have to say, in my experience,

131
00:07:05,974 --> 00:07:08,660
one of the first study I did was

132
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:13,610
about rainwater
recuperation and we

133
00:07:13,610 --> 00:07:17,360
had a program officer
from the CCPA who was

134
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:21,110
leading that and
a remarkable man,

135
00:07:21,110 --> 00:07:22,900
but his boss,

136
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:25,580
at the start of our
study or before

137
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:28,790
even we had signed the contract,

138
00:07:28,790 --> 00:07:32,000
basically said rainwater
recuperation is

139
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:36,205
not useful and not applicable
really in Switzerland.

140
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:38,760
We have enough water,
we don't need that.

141
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:41,580
That was embarrassing
to do that.

142
00:07:41,580 --> 00:07:44,120
The way I got out
of that was to say,

143
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:48,065
let's add to our
study a scenario of

144
00:07:48,065 --> 00:07:52,380
water saving techniques which

145
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:56,295
would certainly or more
likely be of interest,

146
00:07:56,295 --> 00:07:59,450
whereas we also
identified, in some cases,

147
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:03,860
rainwater could be of
interest in sub-sequence set.

148
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:08,845
But it was really a
problem to have in fact,

149
00:08:08,845 --> 00:08:14,300
one of the person
sponsoring the study and

150
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,700
we really had to be
careful to carry

151
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:19,720
out a very independent
work in that case.

152
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:23,480
The independence is
also ensured via

153
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:27,425
optional peer reviewers
and these are

154
00:08:27,425 --> 00:08:31,570
really scientists,
independent LCA experts.

155
00:08:31,570 --> 00:08:32,990
Could be also from a company,

156
00:08:32,990 --> 00:08:36,410
but they are really knowledgeable
in LCA and they are

157
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:37,700
chosen by the sponsor and

158
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:40,190
the study author but should
be independent of you.

159
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:43,390
That's not the people you
work on a weekly basis with.

160
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:45,625
It's not people
within your business,

161
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:50,460
it's people outside which
will give credibility.